sequenceDiagram
    actor Customer
    participant API as HTTP handler
    participant UC as PlaceOrder
    participant Pool as Worker pool
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant Pay as Payment gateway
    participant Bus as Event bus
    participant Async as Notifications and Audit

    Customer->>API: POST /api/v1/orders (JWT, items)
    API->>UC: Handle
    UC->>DB: FindByIdempotencyKey
    alt order already exists
        DB-->>UC: existing order
        UC-->>API: 200 OK
    else new order
        UC->>DB: load products, snapshot prices
        UC->>Pool: submit, then wait
        Pool->>DB: Tx1 create order, reserve stock
        Note over DB: UPDATE ... WHERE available >= qty<br/>0 rows means out of stock, rollback
        Pool->>Pay: charge, idempotent with retry and backoff
        Pool->>DB: Tx2 commit stock and fulfil<br/>or release stock and fail
        UC->>Bus: publish domain events
        Bus--)Async: dispatch, non-blocking
        UC-->>API: 201 Created
    end
    API-->>Customer: order JSON
